Boil a #pot{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} for your noodles. Peel the @ginger{1} with the edge of a spoon and dice finely. Peel and finely dice the @garlic cloves{3}. Remove the core from the @red pepper{2} and slice very thinly (into batons). Slice the @red chilli{1} lengthways, remove the seeds and finely dice.

Chop the @onion{1/2} in half through the root and peel off the skin. Chop both the very top and bottom off and slice very thinly lengthways.

> This technique will give you 'half-moon' shapes.

Put the @egg noodle nests{3} in the boiling water for ~{3%mins} then drain them. Refill the pan with cold water, put the noodles back in and keep the pan to the side.

> The noodles should be just soft enough to eat, so test them before draining. This will stop them cooking and keep them from sticking together.

Chop the @British chicken thighs{6} into small pieces (the size of a 10 pence piece). Heat @oil{2%tsp} in a #non-stick pan{} on high heat. Once very hot add in the chicken with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook for ~{6-8%mins} until browned off then remove from the pan.

In the same pan add @oil{1%tbsp} on high heat. Once hot, add the garlic, ginger and as much chilli as you dare. After ~{30%secs} add in the red pepper and onion and cook until soft (~{4%mins}). Lastly, add the @curry powder mix{4} with @water{3%tbsp}.

Drain the noodles and add to the pan with the @beansprouts{1}, toss everything together. Add in the @soy sauce{4} and continue to toss the ingredients for a few mins. Add the chicken back into the pan. Snip @chives{1}(snipped) and toss these in as well.

Serve the noodles in #bowls{} with a really good squeeze of @lime{1} juice on top. Scatter over a few more snips of chives. Tuck in!